<!-- THE MEASUREMENT ZOO -->
<section class="chaos" id="chaos">

  <div class="section-label">It's not your fault</div>
  <h2 class="section-title">There's a reason you can't give a straight answer.</h2>
  <p class="section-desc">95+ vendors. 6 competing methods. Every one of them says they're the solution. This is the landscape you're supposed to navigate while also hitting your numbers.</p>

  <div class="chaos-grid">
    <div class="chaos-card" data-delay="0">
      <div class="chaos-card-icon" style="background: rgba(255, 77, 106, 0.08);"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="var(--red)"><path d="M12 9v4m0 4h.01M12 3l9.5 16.5H2.5L12 3z" /></svg></div>
      <h3>Platform Attribution</h3>
      <div class="vendors">Google Ads &middot; Meta &middot; TikTok &middot; LinkedIn &middot; Amazon</div>
      <p>Every channel grades its own homework. Combined, they claim 2&ndash;3x your actual conversions. Try explaining that to your CFO.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="chaos-card" data-delay="100">
      <div class="chaos-card-icon" style="background: rgba(77, 127, 255, 0.08);"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="var(--accent)"><path d="M8 3v3a2 2 0 01-2 2H3m18 0h-3a2 2 0 01-2-2V3m0 18v-3a2 2 0 012-2h3M3 16h3a2 2 0 012 2v3" /></svg></div>
      <h3>Multi-Touch Attribution</h3>
      <div class="vendors">mbuzz &middot; Northbeam &middot; Triple Whale &middot; Rockerbox &middot; Cometly &middot; Ruler</div>
      <p>Distributes credit across touchpoints. Better than last-click. But 20+ vendors all claiming different numbers. Which one do you trust?</p>
    </div>
    <div class="chaos-card" data-delay="200">
      <div class="chaos-card-icon" style="background: rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.08);"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="#a78bfa"><path d="M3 3v18h18" /><path d="M7 16l4-8 4 4 4-8" /></svg></div>
      <h3>Media Mix Modeling</h3>
      <div class="vendors">Mutinex &middot; Recast &middot; Meridian &middot; Robyn &middot; Paramark</div>
      <p>Statistical models that work without cookies. But you need $2M+ in spend and months of data before they're reliable. Not exactly a quick win.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="chaos-card" data-delay="300">
      <div class="chaos-card-icon" style="background: rgba(77, 255, 145, 0.08);"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="var(--green)"><path d="M22 12h-4l-3 9L9 3l-3 9H2" /></svg></div>
      <h3>Incrementality Testing</h3>
      <div class="vendors">Haus &middot; Measured &middot; LiftLab</div>
      <p>The gold standard &mdash; actual causal proof. But it means turning off channels for weeks and hoping you were right. $5M+ spend minimum. 3 vendors.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="chaos-card" data-delay="400">
      <div class="chaos-card-icon" style="background: rgba(255, 159, 77, 0.08);"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="var(--orange)"><path d="M18 20V10m-6 10V4M6 20v-6" /></svg></div>
      <h3>Analytics Platforms</h3>
      <div class="vendors">GA4 &middot; Adobe &middot; Mixpanel &middot; Amplitude &middot; PostHog</div>
      <p>GA4 removed most attribution models in 2023. Everyone still uses it as a source of truth. It tells you what happened. Not whether your spend caused it.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="chaos-card" data-delay="500">
      <div class="chaos-card-icon" style="background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="var(--text-muted)"><ellipse cx="12" cy="5" rx="9" ry="3" /><path d="M21 12c0 1.66-4.03 3-9 3s-9-1.34-9-3" /><path d="M3 5v14c0 1.66 4.03 3 9 3s9-1.34 9-3V5" /></svg></div>
      <h3>Server-Side &amp; CDPs</h3>
      <div class="vendors">Segment &middot; RudderStack &middot; Snowplow &middot; Stape &middot; Tealium</div>
      <p>Essential plumbing. Captures better data. But 16+ vendors and none of them answers the question your CFO is actually asking.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="chaos-punchline fade-in">
    <p><span class="stat">95+ vendors. 6 methods. Zero consensus.</span><br>This is why &ldquo;is marketing working?&rdquo; is the hardest question in business. Most teams can't answer it. The first step is knowing where you actually stand.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- THE FOUR LEVELS -->
<section class="levels" id="levels">

  <div class="section-label">The framework</div>
  <h2 class="section-title">Four levels of confidence in your spend.</h2>
  <p class="section-desc">Each level answers a harder question. Most teams are stuck at Level 1 &mdash; relying on the same platforms they're trying to measure.</p>

  <div class="levels-stack">
    <div class="level-row" data-delay="0">
      <div class="level-indicator" style="background: rgba(255, 77, 106, 0.08); color: var(--red);">1</div>
      <div class="level-content">
        <h3>Ad Hoc</h3>
        <div class="tagline">"The platforms say it's working, so it must be working"</div>
        <div class="detail">Each channel grades its own homework. When the CFO asks for proof, you open a dashboard and hope the numbers look good enough.</div>
        <div class="level-callout">&#8592; Most companies are here</div>
      </div>
      <div class="level-meta">
        <div class="spend">Any spend</div>
        <div class="pct">Most companies</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="level-row" data-delay="150">
      <div class="level-indicator" style="background: rgba(77, 127, 255, 0.08); color: var(--accent);">2</div>
      <div class="level-content">
        <h3>Operational</h3>
        <div class="tagline">"We have our own numbers, not just the platform's"</div>
        <div class="detail">Independent tracking. Cross-channel deduplication. You can answer &ldquo;what happened?&rdquo; with confidence. You're still working out &ldquo;did it actually work?&rdquo;</div>
      </div>
      <div class="level-meta">
        <div class="spend">$60K+/yr spend</div>
        <div class="pct"></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="level-row" data-delay="300">
      <div class="level-indicator" style="background: rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.08); color: #a78bfa;">3</div>
      <div class="level-content">
        <h3>Analytical</h3>
        <div class="tagline">"We cross-check before we commit budget"</div>
        <div class="detail">MTA and MMM triangulated. When methods disagree, you investigate instead of panic. You can walk into a board meeting with a real answer.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="level-meta">
        <div class="spend">$500K+/yr spend</div>
        <div class="pct"></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="level-row" data-delay="450">
      <div class="level-indicator" style="background: rgba(77, 255, 145, 0.08); color: var(--green);">4</div>
      <div class="level-content">
        <h3>Leader</h3>
        <div class="tagline">"We can prove it. Causally."</div>
        <div class="detail">Controlled experiments prove what's actually driving revenue. Budget flows to proven winners automatically. When the CFO asks, you don't flinch.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="level-meta">
        <div class="spend">$2M+/yr spend</div>
        <div class="pct">Very few companies</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="evidence-callout fade-in">
    <p><strong>The biggest ROI is moving from Level 1 to Level 2.</strong> Dropbox's data science team found that platform attribution overstates performance by 2&ndash;10x. Even at $100K ad spend, that's $20K&ndash;$50K in budget you can't defend &mdash; every year. MTA tools that fix this start at $29/month.</p>
    <div class="source">Chivukula, Jin &amp; Zhan &mdash; "From Attribution to Causality in Digital Advertising," IEEE Access, March 2026</div>
  </div>
</section>

